import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='num_dependencies', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['num_dependencies'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['num_dependencies'].median()))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of number of dependencies between software packages?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='num_dependencies', ascending=False)
    chart = sns.barplot(x='target', y='num_dependencies', data=data)
    chart.axhline(y=data['num_dependencies'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Max: {data['num_dependencies'].max():.2f}")
    chart.legend(loc='upper right')
    return chart

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.copy()
    data['num_dependencies'] = pd.to_numeric(data['num_dependencies'], errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='num_dependencies', data=data, ax=ax, color='skyblue')
    ax.axvline(data['num_dependencies'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['num_dependencies'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average number of dependencies per software package?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
